---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { snippetStep, snippetRoute, snippetToPass } from '../../../content/snippets/playwright-tricks-en';

const title = '5 Playwright Tricks That Saved Me Hours';
const date = 'March 25, 2026';
const readTime = '6 min read';

const stepHeading = '1. test.step() for readable reports';
const routeHeading = '2. page.route() to mock APIs';
const toPassHeading = '3. expect().toPass() with retries';
const lastFailedHeading = '4. The --last-failed flag';
const traceHeading = '5. Trace viewer over screenshots alone';

const traceOptTok = "trace: 'on-first-retry'";
const parallelConfigureTok = "test.describe.configure({ mode: 'parallel' })";
---

<BaseLayout
  locale="en"
  title={`${title} — Santiago Zapata Mejía`}
  description="Five practical Playwright patterns: test.step, route mocking, toPass, --last-failed, and the trace viewer."
>
  <article class="article">
    <div class="article-container">
      <a href="/en/blog" class="back-link">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M13 8H3M7 4L3 8l4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        Back to blog
      </a>

      <header class="article-header fade-in">
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span class="article-tag">Playwright</span>
          <span class="article-date">{date} · {readTime}</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="article-title">{title}</h1>
        <p class="article-subtitle">
          I've used Playwright daily for years. These five tricks saved me more hours than I'd like to admit — and you can drop them into your suite today.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="article-body fade-in">
        <p>
          For a production-ready layout with POM, fixtures, and CI, see my open source framework:
          <a href="https://github.com/ZapataMejia/playwright-automation-framework" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">playwright-automation-framework</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>{stepHeading}</h2>
        <p>
          Wrap logical blocks in named steps. When a test fails at 2am, the report tells you which phase broke — not just a generic stack line.
        </p>
        <pre class="mono-block"><span class="mono-inner">{snippetStep}</span></pre>

        <h2>{routeHeading}</h2>
        <p>
          Stop depending on flaky staging. Intercept the URL, return stable JSON, and focus on the UI flow.
        </p>
        <pre class="mono-block"><span class="mono-inner">{snippetRoute}</span></pre>

        <h2>{toPassHeading}</h2>
        <p>
          Instead of brittle <span class="tok">waitForTimeout</span> hacks, let Playwright retry the assertion until it passes or times out. Cleaner and more stable.
        </p>
        <pre class="mono-block"><span class="mono-inner">{snippetToPass}</span></pre>

        <h2>{lastFailedHeading}</h2>
        <p>
          Re-run only what broke. On a 400+ test suite, this alone cut my debug time in half.
        </p>

        <h2>{traceHeading}</h2>
        <p>
          Screenshots are 2015. The trace gives you the full timeline: network, DOM snapshots, console, and actions. Use <span class="tok">{traceOptTok}</span> or <span class="tok">retain-on-failure</span> in CI and open the artifact in the local viewer.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Bonus:</strong> combine <span class="tok">{parallelConfigureTok}</span> with sharding in CI and watch a 20-minute pipeline drop toward five minutes on large projects.
        </p>

        <div class="article-author">
          <div class="author-info">
            <div class="author-avatar">SZ</div>
            <div>
              <div class="author-name">Santiago Zapata Mejía</div>
              <div class="author-role">QA Automation Lead · Speaker at QAConf Eje Cafetero</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a href="/en/blog" class="back-link back-link-bottom">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M13 8H3M7 4L3 8l4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        Back to blog
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article { padding: 120px 0 80px; }
  .article-container { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
  .back-link {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
    font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-tertiary); transition: color var(--transition); margin-bottom: 48px;
  }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .back-link-bottom { margin-bottom: 0; margin-top: 48px; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 48px; padding-bottom: 40px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .article-meta { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .article-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--accent);
    padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 100px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.25); background: var(--accent-dim);
  }
  .article-date { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-tertiary); }
  .article-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
    font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .article-subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .article-body { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .article-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5em; }
  .article-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text); margin-top: 2.5em; margin-bottom: 0.8em; letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .article-body strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }
  .article-body a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .article-body .tok {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace; font-size: 0.88em;
    background: var(--bg-elevated); padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--accent);
  }
  .article-body pre.mono-block {
    margin-bottom: 1.8em; border-radius: 12px; overflow-x: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #0d0d0d;
  }
  .article-body pre.mono-block .mono-inner {
    display: block; padding: 24px; background: none; border: none;
    color: #c9d1d9; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.7; white-space: pre; overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
  }
  .article-author {
    margin-top: 64px; padding: 32px; border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg-elevated);
  }
  .author-info { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; }
  .author-avatar {
    width: 48px; height: 48px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--accent-dim);
    color: var(--accent); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-heading); font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .author-name { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text); }
  .author-role { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-top: 2px; }
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .article { padding: 100px 0 60px; }
    .article-body pre.mono-block .mono-inner { font-size: 0.78rem; padding: 16px; }
    .article-author { padding: 24px; }
    .author-info { flex-direction: column; text-align: center; }
  }
</style>
